41/* This alias set can be used to force a memory to conflict with all
42 other memories, creating a barrier across which no memory reference
43 can move. Note that there are other legacy ways to create such
44 memory barriers, including an address of SCRATCH. */
45#define ALIAS_SET_MEMORY_BARRIER ((alias_set_type) -1)
